OL,3,CLarijani's death would be a symbolic
OL,4,CUS-Israel victory but not a decisive
OL,5,Cone
OL,7,FThere is no doubting he was a
OL,8,Fsignificant figure in the Islamic
OL,9,FRepublic. He did carry power, he was a
OL,10,Fdecision maker, and in the progression
OL,11,Fof this war, he was critical. He had
OL,12,Falso been a key advisor to the late
OL,13,FAyatollah.
OL,15,FBut Iran is not Iraq or Libya. It is a
OL,16,Fcountry built on institutions,
OL,17,Fdiscreet units of power, not a one-man
OL,18,Fpower structure. The death of the
OL,19,FSupreme Leader has not led to defeat,
OL,20,Fand the death of another politician
OL,21,Fwill not either.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
