OL,3,CLarijani's death would be a symbolic
OL,4,CUS-Israel victory but not a decisive
OL,5,Cone
OL,7,FLarijani was one of those who
OL,8,Fnegotiated the original Iran nuclear
OL,9,Fdeal back in 2015. He had studied
OL,10,FWestern culture, written about
OL,11,Fphilosophy, and briefly enrolled at
OL,12,FBerkeley in California. He came from a
OL,13,Ffamily steeped in Iranian society, his
OL,14,Ffather a respected cleric, his
OL,15,Fbrothers deep in the political system.
OL,16,FIn 2009, Times magazine described the
OL,17,Ffamily dynasty as "Kennedys of Iran".
OL,19,FHowever, he was also politically
OL,20,Fruthless and loathed by those who
OL,21,Fsought a different path for Iran.
OL,26,@yD@SOUyD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/5
